reviewText: Even without already knowing that this series was canceled, you do get a feeling that the end was near. The humans are starting to shake off their dependence on the Taelons and the Taelons are themselves in serious trouble. As always, many of the better shows end up being axed and the crappy ones seem to go on forever. Sad that, unlike the original Star Trek, EFC did not continue on in syndication. There is one bad thing. The packaging of the discs is a very poor design. The discs ore overlaying each other and the case does not hold them secure. As a result, the DVDs fall out of the case and slide around each other, thus risking the chance of being scratched. Not sure who the Einstein was that designed this case, but they should have been kicked in the backside for this poor desin. If you are thinking of getting season five, as well, be advised the DVDs are packaged in the same style.
Title: Earth: Final Conflict - Season Four

reviewText: An import, it delivered wide screen viewing and good audio, but lacked English subtitles for the hearing impaired.  I will upgrade when I find a better version.

reviewText: Although none of the actors were familiar to me, they were superb.  The series concept was well-thought out and the sets and special effects were great.  Often, sci-fi movies/series can be cheesy with substandard music and dialogue, but it's easy to get caught up in and remain fascinated by this series.  What's really good is that since there so many different plots going on in the series, the intro to each episode connects what's about to be shown with what has already transpired in that plot line.  Each season continues the same high quality.
Title: Earth: Final Conflict - Season Four

reviewText: It has gotten unpredictable with the a lot of the main characters being killed off but but I love the ending episodes which brought it altogether.  Where is the next season going?  Who knows?!

reviewText: This Sci-Fi Drama was exactly as I remembered it, the reason I gave a four was because of the packaging. The manufacturing folks could have really just gone with a simpler system and had better protection for the disc. In 4 of the 5 seasons I purchased, there were discs flopping around inside the box. Luckly there wasn't any damage.
